}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E1_30_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E1_30_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Unlicensed premises owner }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8212\'3f}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ under eighteen years of age consumption or possession.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For first offense violations of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 123.47, subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is two hundred sixty dollars.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{9.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E11_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E11_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Notification violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For violations of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 229.22, subsection 6}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is one thousand dollars for a first violation and two thousand dollars for a second or subsequent violation. The scheduled fine under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is a civil penalty, and the crime services surcharge under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 911.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not be added to the penalty.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{10.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E12_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E12_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Scrap metal transaction violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For violations of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 714.27}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is one hundred dollars for a first violation, five hundred dollars for a second violation within two years, and one thousand dollars for a third or subsequent violation within two years. The scheduled fine under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is a civil penalty which shall be deposited into the general fund of the county or city if imposed by a designated officer or employee of a county or city, or deposited in the general fund of the state if imposed by a state agency, and the crime services surcharge under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 911.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not be added to the penalty.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E13_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E13_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Used catalytic converter transaction violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For violations of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 714.27A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is one thousand dollars for a first violation, five thousand dollars for a second violation within two years, and ten thousand dollars for a third or subsequent violation within two years. The scheduled fine under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is a civil penalty which shall be deposited into the general fund of the county or city if imposed by a designated officer or employee of a county or city, or deposited in the general fund of the state if imposed by a state agency, and the crime services surcharge under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 911.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not be added to the penalty.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E14_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E14_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Trespassing violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For trespasses punishable under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 716.8, subsection 1 or 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is five hundred dollars for a first violation, one thousand dollars for a second violation, and one thousand five hundred dollars for a third or subsequent violation.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{13.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E15_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E15_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Internet fantasy sports contest violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For violations of legal age for entering an internet fantasy sports contest under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 99E.7}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the scheduled fine is five hundred dollars. Failure to pay the fine by a person under the age of eighteen shall not result in the person being detained in a secure facility.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{14.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E17_2E16_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E17_2E16_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{State park user fee violations.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For failure to pay the entrance fee by a nonresident operator of a vehicle under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 455A.14A, subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{,* or under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 455A.14B, subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{,** the scheduled fine is fifteen dollars.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2001 Acts, ch 137, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1111, \'a75, 6}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1118, \'a77, 11}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1127, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1136, \'a758}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 15, \'a79, 14}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 105, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 179, \'a7140}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 173, \'a79}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2008 Acts, ch 1084, \'a715}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2009 Acts, ch 88, \'a75}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2010 Acts, ch 1103, \'a73}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2010 Acts, ch 1128, \'a77}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2010 Acts, ch 1190, \'a719}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1099, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1026, \'a7142}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1096, \'a77}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1109, \'a713}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 99, \'a755}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2017 Acts, ch 140, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2019 Acts, ch 132, \'a743, 45, 46}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1074, \'a744, 57, 93}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2022 Acts, ch 1092, \'a76}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2024 Acts, ch 1070, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2024 Acts, ch 1154, \'a724}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2024 Acts, ch 1176, \'a716}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a799B.54}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 99B.57}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 99D.11}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 99E.7}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 99F.9}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 123.47}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 123.50}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 126.23A}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 142D.9}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 204.14E}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 229.22}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 321.486}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 453A.3}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 473.8}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 716.8}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 725.19}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 803.3}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.6}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8A(12)(e)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.11}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{*Section 455A.14A repealed by its own terms effective December 31, 2025; corrective legislation is pending}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{**Section 455A.14B repealed by its own terms effective December 31, 2025; corrective legislation is pending}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.9}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E18_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E18_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Admission of scheduled violations.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{In cases of scheduled violations, the defendant, before the time specified in the citation and complaint for appearance before the court, may sign the admission of violation on the citation and complaint and deliver or mail a copy of the citation and complaint, together with the minimum fine for the violation, plus court costs, to a scheduled violations office in the county. The office shall, if the offense is a moving violation under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 321}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, forward an abstract of the citation and complaint and admission to the state department of transportation as required by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.491}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. In this case the defendant is not required to appear before the court. The admission constitutes a conviction.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A defendant charged with a scheduled violation by information may obtain two copies of the information from the court and, before the time the defendant is required to appear before the court, deliver or mail the copies, together with the defendant\u8217\'3fs admission, fine, and court costs, to the scheduled violations office in the county. The procedure, fine, and costs are the same as when the charge is by citation and complaint, with the admission and the number of the defendant\u8217\'3fs driver\u8217\'3fs license as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ placed upon the information when the violation involves the use of a motor vehicle.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.8}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ are applicable but the officer does not deem it advisable to release the defendant and no court in the county is in session:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the defendant wishes to admit the violation, the officer may release the defendant upon observing the person mail the citation and complaint, admission, and minimum fine, together with court costs, to a traffic violations office in the county, in an envelope furnished by the officer. The admission constitutes a conviction and judgment in the amount of the scheduled fine plus court costs. The officer may allow the defendant to use a credit card pursuant to rules adopted under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.14}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ by the department of public safety or to mail a check in the proper amount in lieu of cash. If the check is not paid by the drawee for any reason, the defendant may be held in contempt of court. The officer shall advise the defendant of the penalty for nonpayment of the check.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the defendant does not comply with paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the officer may release the defendant upon observing the defendant mail to a court in the county the citation and complaint and one and one-half times the minimum fine together with court costs, or in lieu of one and one-half times the fine and the court costs, a guaranteed arrest bond certificate as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.1, subsection 30}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, as bail together with the following statement signed by the defendant:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb80\ri1084\li1084\sa80{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{I agree that either (1) I will appear pursuant to this citation or (2) if I do not appear in person or by counsel to defend against the offense charged in this citation the court is authorized to enter a conviction and render judgment against me for the amount of one and one-half times the scheduled fine plus court costs.}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{If the defendant does not comply with paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ or }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, or when }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 804.7}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is applicable, the officer may arrest and confine the defendant if authorized by the latter section, and proceed according to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 804}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A defendant who admits a scheduled violation may appear before court. The procedure, costs, and fine, without suspension of the fine, after the hearing are the same as in the traffic violations office.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A defendant charged with a scheduled violation who does not fully comply with }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1, 2, 3, or 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ before the time required to appear before the court must, at that time, appear before the court. If the defendant admits the violation, the procedure, costs, and fine, without suspension of the fine, after the hearing are the same before the court as before the traffic violations office, and are without prejudice, when applicable, to proceedings under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.487}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{6.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The court costs imposed by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ are the total costs collectible from a defendant upon either an admission of a violation without hearing, or upon a hearing pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, 75, 77, \'a7753.16; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.9}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1104, \'a727}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 186, \'a710131, 10201}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 204, \'a710}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{85 Acts, ch 195, \'a763}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{85 Acts, ch 197, \'a742}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1230, \'a795}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{98 Acts, ch 1073, \'a79}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7716.8}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.6}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8A(12)(e)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8C(3)(a)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8C(3)(c)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8C(3)(d)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.10}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.10}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E19_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E19_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Required court appearance.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Section 805.9}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall not apply to a scheduled violation in any of the following circumstances:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When the violation charged involved or resulted in a death or caused serious injury to person as defined under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 702.18}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When the violation charged involved or resulted in an accident or injury to property and based upon the violator\u8217\'3fs driving record, or failure to pay any fine, surcharge, or court costs, or any other circumstances involving the accident, the officer determines a court appearance is necessary.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When the violation created an immediate threat to the safety of other persons or property because of highway conditions, visibility, traffic, repetition, or other circumstances.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When the violation charged involves the taking of an animal for which there is a civil damage assessment in addition to a criminal penalty.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{e.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{When a violation charged involves the consumption, possession, purchase, or attempt to purchase of a consumable hemp product as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 204.14E}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, for which there is a community service sentence.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{In such cases, the defendant shall appear before the court and regular procedure shall apply. If an information is used, the officer shall endorse thereon, \u8220\'3fCourt appearance required\u8221\'3f. If a citation and complaint is used, the officer shall strike out the space in which the defendant may admit the violation before a scheduled violations office and shall endorse thereon \u8220\'3fCourt appearance required\u8221\'3f and the defendant shall appear before the court either in person or by attorney.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, 75, 77, \'a7753.17; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.10}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 125, \'a79}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{84 Acts, ch 1067, \'a750}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{89 Acts, ch 296, \'a792}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1216, \'a75}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{98 Acts, ch 1178, \'a715}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1131, \'a74, 5}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1154, \'a742}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2024 Acts, ch 1176, \'a717}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7204.14E}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.6}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8A(12)(e)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.11}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.13}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.11}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E2_30_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E2_30_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Other penalties.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{If the defendant is convicted of a scheduled violation, the penalty is the scheduled fine, without suspension of the fine prescribed in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.8A}}}{, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.8B}}}{, or }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.8C}}}{ together with costs assessed and distributed as prescribed by }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 602.8106}}}{, unless it appears from the evidence that the violation was of the type set forth in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.10, subsection 1}}}{, paragraph }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{ or }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{, in which event the scheduled fine does not apply and the penalty shall be increased within the limits provided by law for the offense.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, 75, 77, \'a7753.18; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.11}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{82 Acts, ch 1104, \'a728}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 186, \'a710132, 10201}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{85 Acts, ch 195, \'a764}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2000 Acts, ch 1154, \'a743}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2001 Acts, ch 137, \'a75}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8A(12)(e)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.12}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E21_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E21_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Disposition of traffic fines and costs.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Fines, forfeiture of bail, fees, and costs collected for all traffic violations, whether or not scheduled, and for all other scheduled violations shall be distributed in accordance with }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 602.8106}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, 75, 77, \'a7753.19; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.12}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{83 Acts, ch 186, \'a710133, 10201}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8A(14)(f)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.8C(3)(d)}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.13}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E22_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E22_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Venue.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Traffic violations, whether or not scheduled, and all other scheduled violations may be tried before the nearest magistrate in the judicial district in which the offense is committed, or if the offense occurred in a city which is located in two counties, the violation shall be tried as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 803.3, subsection 5}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Upon written consent of the defendant and the officer issuing the citation, traffic violations, whether or not scheduled, and any other scheduled violations, other than those for which a court appearance is required under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ may be prosecuted in any county in the state irrespective of where committed, and in such event the documents in the case shall be sent to the court or traffic and scheduled violations office designated by the defendant and the officer.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C73, 75, 77, \'a7753.20; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.13}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2003 Acts, ch 113, \'a73}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2004 Acts, ch 1041, \'a72}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7803.3}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.14}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E23_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E23_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Credit cards.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{Fines for scheduled traffic violations enumerated in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 805.8A}}}{ may be paid by credit cards, as defined in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 537.1301, subsection 17}}}{, approved for that purpose by the commissioner of public safety. The commissioner shall enter agreements with financial institutions extending credit through the use of credit cards to insure reimbursement of the amount of the fine plus appropriate costs to the proper traffic violations office in the state. The commissioner shall adopt rules pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 17A}}}{ to implement the provisions of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C77, \'a7753.21; C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.14}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2001 Acts, ch 137, \'a75}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7805.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.9}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 805.15}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 811.9}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.15}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E24_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E24_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Other citation forms.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The provisions of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 321.485 through 321.487}}}{ shall govern with respect to offenses charged in the manner provided in }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.485}}}{. The provisions of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{sections 805.6 through 805.14}}}{ shall govern with respect to offenses chargeable upon a uniform citation and complaint.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7805.15}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2020 Acts, ch 1063, \'a7380}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7805.1}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{805.16}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E25_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E25_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Citations to persons under eighteen years of age \u8212\'3f arrest \u8212\'3f nonsecure custody.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Except as provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, a peace officer shall issue a police citation or uniform citation and complaint, in lieu of making a warrantless arrest, to a person under eighteen years of age accused of committing a simple misdemeanor under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 321}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{321G}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{321I}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{461A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{461B}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{462A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{481A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{481B}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{483A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{484A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{484B}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, or a local ordinance not subject to the jurisdiction of the juvenile court, and shall not detain or confine the person in a facility regulated under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 356}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ or }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{356A}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person under the age of eighteen who refuses to sign the citation without qualification, who persists in engaging in the conduct for which the citation was issued, who refuses to provide proper identification or to identify the person\u8217\'3fs self, or who constitutes an immediate threat to the person\u8217\'3fs own safety or the safety of the public may be arrested in the manner provided in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. In addition, or alternatively, the peace officer may require that person to surrender the person\u8217\'3fs driver\u8217\'3fs license as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 321.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ until the time of the person\u8217\'3fs initial court appearance. The peace officer shall immediately send the person\u8217\'3fs driver\u8217\'3fs license along with a copy of the unsigned citation indicating the juvenile\u8217\'3fs refusal to sign to the clerk of the district court for the district in which the peace officer issued the citation.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person arrested pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall only be arrested for the limited purpose of holding the person in nonsecure custody in an area not intended for secure detention while awaiting transfer to an appropriate juvenile facility or to court, for booking, for implied consent testing, for contacting and release to the person\u8217\'3fs parents, or for other administrative purposes.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fnonsecure custody\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means custody in an unlocked multipurpose area, such as a lobby, office, or interrogation room which is not designed, set aside, or used as a secure detention area, and the person arrested is not physically secured during the period of custody in the area, the person is physically accompanied by a peace officer or a person employed by the facility where the person arrested is being held, and the use of the area is limited to providing nonsecure custody only long enough for the purposes stated in paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ and not for a period of time in excess of six hours without the oral or written order of a judge or magistrate authorizing the detention. A judge shall not extend the period of time in excess of six hours beyond the initial six-hour period.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This section}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ does not prohibit the execution of an arrest warrant by a peace officer.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{88 Acts, ch 1167, \'a77}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 90 Acts, ch 1230, \'a796}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 92 Acts, ch 1160, \'a724}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 97 Acts, ch 126, \'a749}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 98 Acts, ch 1073, \'a79}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1132, \'a794}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 30, \'a7220}}}\par}}